 message&#10;@param string $error_code Optional. A Computer readable string to identify the error.&#10;@return false|void" ilk="function" line="1643" lineend="1652" name="bail" returns="false" signature="false bail(string $message, string $error_code = '500')"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="1643" name="message" /><variable citdl="string" default="'500'" ilk="argument" line="1643" name="error_code" /></scope><scope doc="Whether MySQL database is at least the required minimum version.&#10;&#10;@since 2.5.0&#10;@uses $wp_version&#10;@uses $required_mysql_version&#10;&#10;@return WP_Error" ilk="function" line="1663" lineend="1668" name="check_database_version" returns="WP_Error" signature="WP_Error check_database_version()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="1664" name="wp_version" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="1664" name="required_mysql_version" /></scope><scope doc="Whether the database supports collation.&#10;&#10;Called when WordPress is generating the table scheme.&#10;&#10;@since 2.5.0&#10;@deprecated 3.5.0&#10;@deprecated Use wpdb::has_cap( 'collation' )&#10;&#10;@return bool True if collation is supported, false if version does not" ilk="function" line="1681" lineend="1684" name="supports_collation" returns="bool" signature="bool supports_collation()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="The database character collate.&#10;&#10;@since 3.5.0&#10;&#10;@return string The database character collate." ilk="function" line="1693" lineend="1702" name="get_charset_collate" returns="string" signature="string get_charset_collate()"><variable citdl="string" line="1694" name="charset_collate" /></scope><scope doc="Determine if a database supports a particular feature.&#10;&#10;@since 2.7.0&#10;@see wpdb::db_version()&#10;&#10;@param string $db_cap The feature to check for.&#10;@return bool" ilk="function" line="1713" lineend="1726" name="has_cap" returns="bool" signature="bool has_cap(string $db_cap)"><variable citdl="string" il